summary: The script downloads and stores GitHub search results for 'artificial general intelligence' across 13 log files.

details.comment: The script is downloading ten search result pages related to 'artificial general intelligence' from Github, storing each page in separate log files named 0_0.log to 0_9.log.
details.content:
#!/bin/bash
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=1&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_0.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=2&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_1.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=3&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_2.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=4&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_3.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=5&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_4.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=6&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_5.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=7&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_6.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=8&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_7.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=9&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_8.log
wget 'https://github.com/search?p=10&q=artificial+general+intelligence&type=Repositories&utf8=✓' -O 0_9.log

details.comment: The code is making HTTP GET requests to fetch search results on GitHub for the query "artificial general intelligence" in four different pages (p=11 to p=14) and saving the results as 0_10.log, 0_11.log, 0_12.log, and 0_13.log files respectively.
